1
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:27,260
Well, yep. Do you feel like you're rolled in here? We experienced, for the first time, driving on Wednesday before Thanksgiving. Wrong thing to do. I had avoided that all of my life until this year.

2
00:00:28,260 --> 00:00:33,340
And I discovered that half the grandmas in California live in L.A.

3
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:35,880
The other half live outside of L.A.

4
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:39,530
And Wednesday night, everybody's going in and out.

5
00:00:40,170 --> 00:00:41,870
And my goodness, that was a zoo.

6
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:46,170
And I am thankful to be back with this family, safe and sound.

7
00:00:47,030 --> 00:00:51,570
No more road trips, no more kids, no more candy wrappers, no more nothing.

8
00:00:52,250 --> 00:00:53,130
We're back.

9
00:00:53,690 --> 00:00:54,470
It was a good time.

10
00:00:55,420 --> 00:00:57,400
Well, Halloween is now behind us.

11
00:00:57,740 --> 00:01:03,120
We're digesting Thanksgiving, and time is marching forward, is it not?

12
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:07,280
Can you believe we're now in December tomorrow?

13
00:01:07,740 --> 00:01:08,180
Monday.

14
00:01:09,090 --> 00:01:09,750
Close enough.

15
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:14,720
We're moving now towards the end of the year.

16
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:20,780
But we're moving towards the beginning of the celebration of Jesus come into the world.

17
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:25,680
We celebrate at the end of the year.

18
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:31,680
The beginning of the kingdom of God coming to earth in Jesus Christ.

19
00:01:33,050 --> 00:01:43,700
And that celebration is such grand magnitude that our entire dating system is centered around this pivotal event.

20
00:01:45,950 --> 00:01:49,450
Time. Time's an amazing gift.

21
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:53,600
What should our attitude be about time?

22
00:01:54,060 --> 00:01:57,680
How should we handle our time as it's marching forward?

23
00:01:57,680 --> 00:02:01,790
Where is it going and what should we do with it?

24
00:02:02,660 --> 00:02:06,140
I ran across a study by Priority Management Incorporated

25
00:02:06,140 --> 00:02:10,420
and they asserted that the average American will spend, get this,

26
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:16,250
six months sitting at stoplights in your life.

27
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:21,800
You will spend eight months of your life opening junk mail.

28
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:31,440
You will spend a year looking for misplaced objects in your home or garage.

29
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:35,380
It gets worse, you will.

30
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:39,700
Spend two years unsuccessfully returning phone calls,

31
00:02:42,090 --> 00:02:44,650
and you'll spend five years waiting in line.

32
00:02:47,990 --> 00:02:50,290
Someone once said, no wonder time flies.

33
00:02:50,990 --> 00:02:53,270
There are so many people trying to kill it.

34
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:55,620
Isn't that true?

35
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:59,560
Some try and kill time.

36
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:03,700
Others learn tools and techniques to manage our time.

37
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,060
Why is that important?

38
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:10,220
Archbishop Fulton Sheen said this.

39
00:03:10,220 --> 00:03:15,820
He said, every moment comes to you pregnant with a divine purpose.

40
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:22,180
Time being so precious that God deals it out only second by second.

41
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:27,000
Once it leaves your hands and your power to do with it as you please,

42
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:32,840
it plunges into eternity to remain forever what you made it.

43
00:03:34,090 --> 00:03:38,750
A beautiful description about the importance of how we use our time.

44
00:03:39,740 --> 00:03:44,620
What we do with our time leaves the legacy of who we are.

45
00:03:46,340 --> 00:03:51,100
God will hold us accountable for what we do with our time.

46
00:03:53,290 --> 00:03:56,690
And as much as time is moving forward, marching forward,

47
00:03:57,210 --> 00:04:01,770
we cannot, for all practical purposes, change it or manipulate it.

48
00:04:01,770 --> 00:04:03,670
Only we can make choices.

49
00:04:04,530 --> 00:04:07,090
We can only make decisions in time.

50
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:17,140
The reality is that each day that goes forward is a day closer to the return of Jesus Christ.

51
00:04:18,140 --> 00:04:21,060
Time marches forward and it's moving forward.

52
00:04:21,060 --> 00:04:29,720
We can never go back, but it is marching towards the consummation of the ages when Jesus Christ promises to come back.

53
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:36,200
And we cannot change the past.

54
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:42,500
Steven Spielberg, in his marvelous imagination and characters,

55
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:44,760
Marty McFly and the Doc,

56
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:47,340
they can travel back and forth in time

57
00:04:47,340 --> 00:04:50,300
in that wonderful film series, Back to the Future.

58
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,300
Unfortunately, we cannot.

59
00:04:54,780 --> 00:04:59,100
We cannot go back and undo the actions that we regret.

60
00:05:00,370 --> 00:05:02,990
We're always moving forward.

61
00:05:02,990 --> 00:05:10,680
And the challenge for us here is to live proactive lives with no regrets.

62
00:05:12,580 --> 00:05:18,120
We want to look back and see our lives consistent with our goals and our commitments.

63
00:05:18,540 --> 00:05:24,220
For time goes in one direction and the legacy we leave is permanent.

64
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:28,690
And the reason we want to live by our commitments,

65
00:05:29,050 --> 00:05:32,730
the reason we want to manage our time and use it for God's glory

66
00:05:32,730 --> 00:05:36,610
is because Jesus Christ is coming back.

67
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:40,360
And that's the beginning of the Advent season

68
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:44,320
as we prepare for the coming back of our Lord.

69
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:46,180
Our friend Phil Tomic used to say

70
00:05:46,180 --> 00:05:47,860
in all of his letters and his emails,

71
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,640
keep looking up.

72
00:05:53,740 --> 00:05:54,920
Matthew chapter 24.

73
00:05:57,620 --> 00:06:00,740
No one knows about that day or hour.

74
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:04,520
Not even the angels in heaven nor the Son,

75
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:06,520
but only the Father

76
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:09,540
as it was in the days of Noah

77
00:06:09,540 --> 00:06:12,240
so it will be at the coming of the Son of Man

78
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:14,990
for in the days before the flood

79
00:06:14,990 --> 00:06:17,210
people were eating and drinking

80
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:19,430
and marrying and giving in marriage

81
00:06:19,430 --> 00:06:21,870
up to the day Noah entered the ark

82
00:06:21,870 --> 00:06:24,750
and they knew nothing about what would happen

83
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:25,990
until the flood came

84
00:06:25,990 --> 00:06:27,890
and took them all away

85
00:06:27,890 --> 00:06:30,370
that is how it will be

86
00:06:30,370 --> 00:06:31,930
at the coming of the Son of Man

87
00:06:31,930 --> 00:06:34,290
two men will be in the field

88
00:06:34,290 --> 00:06:35,590
one will be taken

89
00:06:35,590 --> 00:06:37,110
and the other left.

90
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:40,220
Two women will be grinding with a hand mill.

91
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:41,460
One will be taken

92
00:06:41,460 --> 00:06:43,220
and the other left.

93
00:06:44,710 --> 00:06:46,890
Therefore, keep watch

94
00:06:46,890 --> 00:06:49,050
because you do not know

95
00:06:49,050 --> 00:06:50,750
on what day your Lord will come.

96
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:52,690
But understand this,

97
00:06:52,890 --> 00:06:54,770
if the owner of the house had known

98
00:06:54,770 --> 00:06:57,110
at what time of night the thief was coming,

99
00:06:57,110 --> 00:06:58,930
he would have kept watch

100
00:06:58,930 --> 00:07:01,710
and would not have let his house be broken into.

101
00:07:02,310 --> 00:07:04,470
So you also must be ready

102
00:07:04,470 --> 00:07:09,670
because the Son of Man will come at an hour when you do not expect Him.

103
00:07:11,980 --> 00:07:17,560
So first point this morning, as we enter Advent season, chin up.

104
00:07:18,710 --> 00:07:21,420
Chin up, church. He's coming back.

105
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:30,460
God came in the person of Jesus Christ, showed us how to live, died for our sins,

106
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:34,440
came back from the dead on Easter to give us heaven.

107
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:40,900
And by accepting who he is and what he did, we become adopted into God's family.

108
00:07:41,540 --> 00:07:44,100
We become children of the King.

109
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,640
He came once as a baby in the manger.

110
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:52,820
Our hope is that he's coming again.

111
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:56,240
We just don't know when.

112
00:07:58,100 --> 00:07:59,400
We don't know when.

113
00:08:00,190 --> 00:08:02,070
The angels don't know when.

114
00:08:02,810 --> 00:08:05,030
Jesus doesn't know when.

115
00:08:05,030 --> 00:08:08,670
Only the Father knows when.

116
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:14,820
And when Jesus says no one knows, he means it.

117
00:08:16,350 --> 00:08:23,400
So when the next author, the next filmmaker, the next radio, television personality

118
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:29,610
predicts a date for Christ's return, they don't really know.

119
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:31,800
Nobody knows.

120
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:34,960
Jesus says nobody knows.

121
00:08:37,090 --> 00:08:43,470
100% of all predictions throughout all of church history about the return of Christ have been wrong.

122
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:47,530
And they all had good reasons.

123
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:54,600
They all lived in an age when it seemed like the signs pointed to the end.

124
00:08:54,740 --> 00:08:56,880
And I don't doubt that it felt real.

125
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:04,320
And Jesus perhaps could have come at those signs.

126
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:05,860
But he didn't.

127
00:09:07,070 --> 00:09:09,890
And only the Father knows when he's coming.

128
00:09:11,110 --> 00:09:13,830
The reality is he will come back.

129
00:09:14,210 --> 00:09:16,430
The when is a different matter.

130
00:09:18,670 --> 00:09:20,290
What we can know is this.

131
00:09:21,930 --> 00:09:24,590
Like in the days of Noah when the floodwaters came,

132
00:09:24,930 --> 00:09:31,930
the people were carrying on with their lives as if everything was going splendidly and swimmingly.

133
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:34,760
And then it happened.

134
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:41,890
If you notice, they're carrying on and marrying and eating and drinking.

135
00:09:42,310 --> 00:09:44,890
It's the everyday stuff of life.

136
00:09:45,110 --> 00:09:47,770
And then it was over, just like that.

137
00:09:49,260 --> 00:09:51,960
And that's the picture Jesus gives us.

138
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:56,260
We're going to carry on, and we're going to be doing the stuff of life,

139
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:58,960
and then boom, he's coming back, just like that.

140
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:01,180
Chin up, church.

141
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:05,370
We don't know when, but he's coming again.

142
00:10:06,370 --> 00:10:10,130
Lift our heads and be ready when he comes.

143
00:10:12,350 --> 00:10:15,610
In light of that certainty, the when is not important.

144
00:10:15,610 --> 00:10:20,450
And in the light of that certainty, the church must, in Jesus' words, be prepared.

145
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:26,440
We must live our lives in case he comes in five minutes from now,

146
00:10:28,810 --> 00:10:30,870
that we might offer him something wonderful.

147
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:41,440
There's a story told about a young couple by the name of Jeff and Janelle and their first date.

148
00:10:43,170 --> 00:10:45,590
Janelle was expecting Jeff to show up.

149
00:10:45,690 --> 00:10:48,070
She was dressed and ready for the date.

150
00:10:48,070 --> 00:10:55,650
She waited patiently for an hour, and he didn't show up.

151
00:10:57,580 --> 00:11:01,820
And so after a while, she finally figured sadly that she'd been stood up,

152
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:06,940
and so she went to the bathroom and took off all her makeup and slipped into her pajamas

153
00:11:06,940 --> 00:11:10,500
and grabbed that pint of ice cream in front of the television

154
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:14,720
and kind of drowned her sorrows in ice cream.

155
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:21,440
And after two hours had passed, guess who shows up at the door?

156
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:24,480
Yeah, it's Jeff.

157
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:25,720
First date.

158
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:31,760
He took one look at her and he said, I'm two hours late and you're still not ready.

159
00:11:36,980 --> 00:11:37,760
It's terrible, I know.

160
00:11:39,340 --> 00:11:42,840
But church, that's how we get to be sometimes as Christians.

161
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:50,760
We expect Jesus to come and then when he doesn't meet the prediction that's on the bestseller list,

162
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:52,820
we just kind of forget about it.

163
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:53,760
We get discouraged.

164
00:11:54,520 --> 00:12:00,180
We need to always be ready because he may come at any time.

165
00:12:01,060 --> 00:12:02,600
We must never slouch.

166
00:12:03,670 --> 00:12:05,750
We must always live expectantly.

167
00:12:09,130 --> 00:12:10,930
We must always keep looking to the sky.

168
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:17,040
And as we move into this season of watching and waiting for the birth of Jesus,

169
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:21,240
we're also watching and waiting for the return of our Lord.

170
00:12:23,290 --> 00:12:25,330
We must, in Jesus' words, keep watch.

171
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:27,400
Keep watch.

172
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:33,460
We must live like Jesus is coming tonight.

173
00:12:33,460 --> 00:12:40,760
And it may not be for a thousand more years, or it might be this afternoon.

174
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:42,420
We don't know.

175
00:12:43,460 --> 00:12:44,060
We don't know.

176
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:45,060
Nobody knows.

177
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,520
Only the Father knows.

178
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:50,340
We must keep chin up and keep watch.

179
00:12:52,610 --> 00:13:02,730
In the tragedy of the 9-11 attacks a couple years ago, there was, for all practical purposes, no warning.

180
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:06,900
Nobody was expecting such a tragedy.

181
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:12,260
Thousands of people that morning got off the subways, out of the taxi cabs,

182
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:17,680
climbed the elevators, went to their offices, and life was simply over just like that.

183
00:13:21,010 --> 00:13:25,970
And I've been thinking about this, and I've come to realize that one of three things can happen to us.

184
00:13:27,170 --> 00:13:32,550
One, we can live a long life until our body finally expires.

185
00:13:33,990 --> 00:13:40,090
Two, we can live our lives full of vim and vigor until it's cut short by an accident,

186
00:13:40,090 --> 00:13:42,510
a health problem, or a tragedy.

187
00:13:44,910 --> 00:13:48,900
Or three, Jesus can come back

188
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:50,820
and life as we know it will cease.

189
00:13:52,130 --> 00:13:54,530
That's really the only three options we have.

190
00:13:54,790 --> 00:13:57,410
We'll live long lives till our body gives it up,

191
00:13:57,830 --> 00:13:59,290
our lives will be cut short,

192
00:13:59,430 --> 00:14:01,530
or Jesus will come today.

193
00:14:01,830 --> 00:14:06,100
If we get really honest,

194
00:14:07,550 --> 00:14:08,870
we really don't know

195
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:11,960
if we're gonna even get home tonight.

196
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:14,240
If we're really honest.

197
00:14:14,970 --> 00:14:16,990
In all probability, probably.

198
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:22,760
But we really don't know, do we?

199
00:14:24,210 --> 00:14:28,670
The Bible says our life is like a blade of grass, a puff of wind.

200
00:14:30,060 --> 00:14:30,980
It comes and it goes.

201
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:37,320
And so my question as I wrestle with this text is, if you were to meet the Lord tonight,

202
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:40,700
what would you present to Him from your life?

203
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,300
What would you present to Him?

204
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:49,260
What would be your Christmas present this season for the Lord?

205
00:14:49,460 --> 00:15:00,250
from your life? Would you even know him? As I've said, time marches forward and actions cannot be

206
00:15:00,250 --> 00:15:07,860
undone. So let us be careful that the record of our lives is what we want our master to encounter

207
00:15:07,860 --> 00:15:19,470
when he returns or when we go to him. Keep watch, says Jesus. Jonathan Edwards, one of the great

208
00:15:19,470 --> 00:15:26,970
early preachers in American history said this. He said, resolved, never do anything which I would

209
00:15:26,970 --> 00:15:38,310
be afraid to do if it were the last hour of my life. If it were the last hour of your life,

210
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:46,680
whatever you're doing, would you want to give that to Jesus? What I'm getting at is this,

211
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:54,700
be ready, keep watch, means to live lives that are holy, that are lived rightly and faithfully

212
00:15:54,700 --> 00:16:06,580
before God. Because disciples, we are to live like disciples. We simply need to act and to live

213
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:13,020
in a way that's consistent with our calling and our citizenship and be ready to meet Jesus

214
00:16:13,020 --> 00:16:19,340
whenever he comes, whenever we meet him. We really don't know when that will be,

215
00:16:19,340 --> 00:16:25,440
But we will live chin up, being ready, keeping watch.

216
00:16:28,980 --> 00:16:32,000
Jerry Bridges, an author, said,

217
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:37,940
Everyone then who professes to be a Christian should ask himself or herself,

218
00:16:39,070 --> 00:16:43,610
Is there evidence of practical holiness in my life?

219
00:16:44,540 --> 00:16:48,120
Do I desire and strive after holiness?

220
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:53,760
Do I grieve over my lack of it earnestly and seek the help of God?

221
00:16:54,180 --> 00:17:04,270
to be holy. As we move into this Advent season, looking forward to the birth of Jesus Christ

222
00:17:04,270 --> 00:17:13,960
and celebrating Emmanuel, God with us, I'd like for us to take a kind of life check,

223
00:17:15,340 --> 00:17:22,190
to look back over the year and ask this question, how is my holiness quotient this year?

224
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:29,470
Am I living my life as if I'm just going through the motions?

225
00:17:31,870 --> 00:17:34,330
Am I living my life with vitality?

226
00:17:36,940 --> 00:17:40,340
Am I living my life with love and grace?

227
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:47,520
Am I living my life as Jesus would live my life?

228
00:17:49,050 --> 00:17:58,720
If Jesus lived in your home, worked in your job, how would he live?

229
00:18:00,940 --> 00:18:02,660
That's the question for us.

230
00:18:02,660 --> 00:18:07,440
we live our lives as Jesus would live our lives

231
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:09,400
in this area

232
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:12,520
with these conditions in this time

233
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:17,360
how would Jesus live your life

234
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:22,540
it's a good thing for us to ponder and ask ourselves these things

235
00:18:22,540 --> 00:18:24,300
because the good news is

236
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:26,760
if we've not lived a life this year

237
00:18:26,760 --> 00:18:29,200
that we're proud to give to the Lord

238
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:32,120
there's forgiveness and there's always a new start

239
00:18:32,120 --> 00:18:34,040
that's the good news

240
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:39,520
We can start over and say, Lord, I want to get out of these patterns.

241
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:45,800
I want to live fresh for you because you're the God of new starts and new beginnings.

242
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:54,740
And so it's good for us to pause, to chin up, to keep watch, to be ready and to ask ourselves,

243
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:59,910
is my life the kind of life I want to give to my King?

244
00:19:02,700 --> 00:19:05,840
We've experienced the fires recently.

245
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:15,340
they burn with intensity don't they there's something we're learning about those fires

246
00:19:15,340 --> 00:19:22,520
though that as they sweep over and they burn up the dead wood and the overgrown ground that when

247
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:28,260
they sweep they're very powerful they're almost frightening as the noise increases and the winds

248
00:19:28,260 --> 00:19:35,050
blow and they're very intense on this trip this weekend i had the privilege and pleasure of

249
00:19:35,050 --> 00:19:37,430
being in the Yosemite Valley for a day.

250
00:19:37,950 --> 00:19:39,470
What a beautiful place that was.

251
00:19:39,550 --> 00:19:42,310
What a majestic, beautiful valley

252
00:19:42,310 --> 00:19:43,570
carved by the glacier.

253
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:46,080
And you can see portions

254
00:19:46,080 --> 00:19:49,140
where recently fire had been.

255
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:52,380
And we drove through some groves of trees

256
00:19:52,380 --> 00:19:54,100
and you see the darkened stumps,

257
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:57,660
but you see the pure ground.

258
00:19:58,520 --> 00:20:00,020
And you see the little saplings

259
00:20:00,020 --> 00:20:01,420
beginning to poke through.

260
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:03,380
You see the new life beginning.

261
00:20:05,770 --> 00:20:07,010
It's an amazing experience

262
00:20:07,010 --> 00:20:15,490
to see how the fire and its destruction can clean away dead and decaying things and bring new life.

263
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:21,020
And friends, in our lives, too, we need to ask the Holy Spirit to come

264
00:20:21,020 --> 00:20:27,080
and to burn away some of the things that hold us back from being all that God wants us to be

265
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:35,160
and allow it to burn away that that new life, the new saplings would grow.

266
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:43,840
Another way to look at this kind of life check, a different way, with a kind of botany twist,

267
00:20:45,940 --> 00:20:49,080
is that there's a number of trees that look very healthy in the summertime.

268
00:20:49,640 --> 00:21:00,790
But in the winter when the leaves have fallen off, there's this parasite that lives on the tree.

269
00:21:02,220 --> 00:21:04,580
Around Christmas, we hang it up and kiss under it.

270
00:21:04,660 --> 00:21:05,540
It's called mistletoe.

271
00:21:05,540 --> 00:21:17,090
But when it's not being sold in bags at tree lots, it clings to trees and sucks the life out of trees.

272
00:21:18,260 --> 00:21:19,080
It's a parasite.

273
00:21:20,510 --> 00:21:28,110
It clings and hangs on and gets its nutrients from the tree and drains the life of the tree.

274
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:36,320
Friends, there can be sin in our lives that can live on our trunks like mistletoe

275
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:39,300
and slowly suck our spiritual vitality

276
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:41,160
right out of our lives.

277
00:21:45,830 --> 00:21:47,230
And as we come into Advent,

278
00:21:49,180 --> 00:21:51,740
as we look forward to the birth of Jesus,

279
00:21:52,620 --> 00:21:54,740
it's a good time to look back

280
00:21:54,740 --> 00:21:56,280
and to ask, Lord,

281
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:59,760
what is it in my life, if anything,

282
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,800
that's sucking down and out

283
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:04,480
my spiritual vitality for you?

284
00:22:06,770 --> 00:22:09,910
Is it time to have the flames of the Spirit blow

285
00:22:09,910 --> 00:22:13,560
and to consume the things that hold you back

286
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:15,880
from living a life before the Lord

287
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:19,280
that you'd be proud to honor when he comes.

288
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:25,340
And so I've got a series of questions I'd like for us

289
00:22:25,340 --> 00:22:28,940
just to collectively ask in our hearts this morning

290
00:22:28,940 --> 00:22:34,870
that we might give it to the Lord

291
00:22:34,870 --> 00:22:39,000
and go forward and start afresh and anew.

292
00:22:41,350 --> 00:22:44,180
How have you done this year at the job?

293
00:22:45,870 --> 00:22:47,910
Your relationships with coworkers,

294
00:22:48,750 --> 00:22:51,820
Have you given your bosses what they're due?

295
00:22:53,850 --> 00:22:56,130
Have you worked as unto the Lord?

296
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:01,200
Have you been ethical in all of your dealings?

297
00:23:06,150 --> 00:23:06,970
What about at home?

298
00:23:09,970 --> 00:23:16,460
How are those relationships within your family, your extended family?

299
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:18,660
Are they healthy?

300
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:25,520
Have you, in the words of Scripture, have you provoked your children to anger?

301
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:34,840
Have you respected your spouse, loved, cared for, respected him or her?

302
00:23:38,330 --> 00:23:45,780
And in your ministry, have you been faithful to God with the spiritual gifts that he has given you?

303
00:23:47,990 --> 00:23:54,100
How's your stewardship of the things he has given in terms of ministry?

304
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,500
Have you invested yourself in the things of God?

305
00:24:00,430 --> 00:24:04,610
Have you served him with joy or with a sour spirit?

306
00:24:04,610 --> 00:24:12,500
Have you been straight up and ethical in all of your dealings with the church and with God's people?

307
00:24:14,350 --> 00:24:15,690
Jesus says, keep watch.

308
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:17,320
Chin up.

309
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:17,980
Be ready.

310
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:26,700
He may come at any moment, and I want my life to honor him.

311
00:24:27,650 --> 00:24:33,970
I want every moment of each day, as it marches forward, to be a gift unto God.

312
00:24:36,930 --> 00:24:40,330
And the good news is, as you're wrestling with these things,

313
00:24:42,730 --> 00:24:47,150
that if you're not pleased with how you've lived up to this point, you can start over.

314
00:24:48,340 --> 00:24:49,400
You can begin again.

315
00:24:50,860 --> 00:24:52,940
Because you can simply confess to the Lord,

316
00:24:52,940 --> 00:24:54,900
Lord, these things have gotten in the way.

317
00:24:54,900 --> 00:24:57,500
they've tangled up in my soul

318
00:24:57,500 --> 00:24:59,440
and I want your spirit to burn them out

319
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:00,500
I want to start over

320
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:02,420
thank you for new beginnings

321
00:25:02,420 --> 00:25:04,920
because like when that fire comes

322
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:07,520
the little saplings start over

323
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:09,920
and new life begins again

324
00:25:09,920 --> 00:25:12,450
praise God for that

325
00:25:12,450 --> 00:25:17,750
and my encouragement to you church

326
00:25:17,750 --> 00:25:18,890
is as we come into Advent

327
00:25:18,890 --> 00:25:22,090
and we're preparing for Jesus coming in the manger

328
00:25:22,090 --> 00:25:24,730
and preparing for Jesus to come again

329
00:25:24,730 --> 00:25:26,390
whenever that might be

330
00:25:26,390 --> 00:25:28,710
that we might be diligent

331
00:25:28,710 --> 00:25:33,400
to live each moment as if he's coming back,

332
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:40,180
as if he's coming back today, tonight, tomorrow.

333
00:25:45,180 --> 00:25:49,720
And a way to do that is to be accountable to somebody else.

334
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:54,820
Too often, I think, we live isolated lives as Christians.

335
00:25:55,420 --> 00:26:00,400
We somehow think between just the Spirit and me, it's all we need.

336
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:04,940
But you know, he designed the church that we might encourage each other.

337
00:26:05,910 --> 00:26:08,570
The Bible talks about iron sharpening iron

338
00:26:08,570 --> 00:26:12,020
as we encourage and rub on each other

339
00:26:12,020 --> 00:26:13,360
and sharpen each other.

340
00:26:15,290 --> 00:26:16,750
So we need each other.

341
00:26:18,380 --> 00:26:19,760
And if you've not told anybody

342
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:22,980
that you desire to live in full integrity

343
00:26:22,980 --> 00:26:25,080
at home, on the job, in my ministry,

344
00:26:25,740 --> 00:26:27,080
and these are my struggles,

345
00:26:28,280 --> 00:26:30,180
I'm going to encourage you this month of December

346
00:26:30,180 --> 00:26:32,360
to find a friend and take them out

347
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:33,340
for lunch or coffee

348
00:26:33,340 --> 00:26:35,520
and be accountable to somebody.

349
00:26:37,110 --> 00:26:46,230
They can ask you and pray for you and encourage you that you'll live chin up, keeping watch, like king's kids.

350
00:26:47,210 --> 00:26:52,630
No parasites of sin, nothing stuck on our branches, sucking our spiritual life away.

351
00:26:53,760 --> 00:26:58,970
No, because somebody else is looking out for you, watching your back for you.

352
00:26:59,370 --> 00:27:05,950
I'm encouraged by some of the men I spend time each week on Monday nights.

353
00:27:08,090 --> 00:27:10,330
And we just go over these kinds of issues each and every week.

354
00:27:10,370 --> 00:27:11,830
How have you been at the job this week?

355
00:27:12,150 --> 00:27:20,110
at home in your ministry, been faithful, been real, been honest, and we share and we pray for

356
00:27:20,110 --> 00:27:25,230
each other. That experience of the church acting as the church, encouraging each other is so

357
00:27:25,230 --> 00:27:33,900
powerful. Can you find a friend? Can you find somebody to encourage, to be encouraged by?

358
00:27:35,010 --> 00:27:42,480
As we desire to live, chin up, keeping watch, that every moment is lived for the glory of God.

359
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:45,410
that's the good news

360
00:27:45,410 --> 00:27:46,510
that's the goal

361
00:27:46,510 --> 00:27:49,990
but I want to say this as we reflect

362
00:27:49,990 --> 00:27:51,910
and prepare for the ending of our time

363
00:27:51,910 --> 00:27:54,530
I'd like for us to take a few moments

364
00:27:54,530 --> 00:27:55,850
in just silent meditation

365
00:27:55,850 --> 00:27:58,660
some silent confession

366
00:27:58,660 --> 00:28:00,480
just quietly, nobody's going to hear it

367
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:02,220
but just your heart and God

368
00:28:02,220 --> 00:28:06,560
and I'm going to encourage you just to bow your heads

369
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:07,120
for a moment

370
00:28:07,120 --> 00:28:11,020
and just ask as we kind of prayerfully think through

371
00:28:11,020 --> 00:28:14,890
how's been our year

372
00:28:14,890 --> 00:28:20,350
are we more mature now

373
00:28:20,350 --> 00:28:21,470
than we were a year ago

374
00:28:21,470 --> 00:28:24,240
what have we learned

375
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:27,100
in the life experiences of this year

376
00:28:27,100 --> 00:28:30,960
are we living each day

377
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:34,050
as if we're a gift unto the Lord

378
00:28:34,050 --> 00:28:37,550
and if not

379
00:28:37,550 --> 00:28:41,380
you can begin to just pray along these lines

380
00:28:41,380 --> 00:28:45,220
Lord I thank you

381
00:28:45,220 --> 00:28:47,120
that you are a merciful

382
00:28:47,120 --> 00:28:48,100
wonderful Lord

383
00:28:48,100 --> 00:28:51,310
that gives us new starts

384
00:28:51,310 --> 00:28:56,890
and Lord whatever these things are

385
00:28:56,890 --> 00:28:58,960
that you brought to mind

386
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:02,420
I confess them before you

387
00:29:02,420 --> 00:29:05,130
I want to remove them

388
00:29:05,130 --> 00:29:09,610
from my life that I might

389
00:29:09,610 --> 00:29:10,770
be pure and holy

390
00:29:10,770 --> 00:29:13,590
living authentic lives with each

391
00:29:13,590 --> 00:29:14,990
and every second that you give

392
00:29:14,990 --> 00:29:19,040
so Lord may all of my life be

393
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:22,100
an act of worship may all

394
00:29:22,100 --> 00:29:23,480
that I am honor you

395
00:29:23,480 --> 00:29:27,680
Lord I pray that you would

396
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:31,120
find a friend an accountability partner

397
00:29:31,120 --> 00:29:33,000
somebody to encourage me that I

398
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:34,100
might encourage as well

399
00:29:34,100 --> 00:29:37,660
we might share heart to heart life to life

400
00:29:37,660 --> 00:29:42,180
as a way to keep watch

401
00:29:42,180 --> 00:29:44,790
to keep our chins up

402
00:29:44,790 --> 00:29:47,880
and live expectantly

403
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:50,030
when you come in the sky.

404
00:29:53,380 --> 00:29:55,860
Father, I pray your spirit upon this congregation

405
00:29:55,860 --> 00:29:57,720
that you would be doing merciful,

406
00:29:57,980 --> 00:29:59,160
wonderful, gracious work.

407
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:03,540
That you'd prune away

408
00:30:03,540 --> 00:30:08,210
the branches that no longer produce fruit.

409
00:30:09,970 --> 00:30:10,970
That you'd revive

410
00:30:10,970 --> 00:30:14,390
and pour the fertilizer of your spirit on our souls.

411
00:30:14,390 --> 00:30:17,680
We might grow and develop and mature.

412
00:30:20,460 --> 00:30:21,560
Lord, keep our eyes,

413
00:30:21,700 --> 00:30:23,620
keep our countenance before you.

414
00:30:24,440 --> 00:30:25,980
Knowing that every moment is a gift.

415
00:30:26,180 --> 00:30:33,280
And may we live it as a gift, one that we give back to you.

416
00:30:36,510 --> 00:30:38,210
Forgive us, Lord, for our wrongs.

417
00:30:38,310 --> 00:30:39,990
Forgive us for the things that don't honor you.

418
00:30:41,340 --> 00:30:42,440
Clean us afresh.

419
00:30:42,620 --> 00:30:44,240
Make us ready for 2004.

420
00:30:47,140 --> 00:30:52,980
May we live lives of victory, overcoming new hurdles, new obstacles,

421
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:55,920
because we're trusting in you.

422
00:30:56,260 --> 00:30:57,600
We're filled by your spirit.

423
00:31:01,420 --> 00:31:02,500
We're looking chin up.

424
00:31:02,820 --> 00:31:09,400
So, Lord, take all that we are and mold it for your glory.

425
00:31:12,150 --> 00:31:13,130
My life is yours.

426
00:31:15,100 --> 00:31:16,160
It's all yours.

427
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:19,400
Thank you for your mercy and your grace.

428
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:20,620
Thank you for the Spirit.

429
00:31:21,600 --> 00:31:23,040
Thank you for new beginnings.

430
00:31:24,990 --> 00:31:26,370
Thank you for life eternal.

431
00:31:28,820 --> 00:31:30,720
Thank you that Jesus will one day come.

432
00:31:32,480 --> 00:31:33,260
And may we be ready.

433
00:31:35,010 --> 00:31:36,010
In Jesus' name.

